<div class="generalitem newsitem"><strong>2012-01-26</strong> (<a href="newsitem.cgi/1327584490" title="Permanent link" rel="bookmark">#</a>) <span class="age">1 year ago</span>
<blockquote>After the <a href="http://idefix.net/~koos/newsitem.cgi/1327263605">updates to virtualbookcase.com last weekend</a>
I noticed one other area of serious bit rot: character set damage. The pages
were still charset=US-ASCII and this went noticeably wrong in
<a href="http://www.virtualbookcase.com/book/detail/45000245/HTML-For-Dummies">HTML For Dummies® by Ed Tittel and Steve James</a>.
But there are only a few places where I had to change that, and the databases
are all UTF8 anyway.
<p></p>
Funny is how the amount of visitors is slowly growing since this weekend.
A few improvements and a few new links from my homepage, and suddenly more
visitors.</blockquote>
