<div class="generalitem newsitem"><strong>2011-02-09</strong> (<a href="newsitem.cgi/1297260948" title="Permanent link" rel="bookmark">#</a>) <span class="age">2 years ago</span>
<blockquote>I wanted a global option to deny access to any phpmyadmin url in an apache
config. We are migrating long-existing websites with sometimes old content
to new hardware and storage. And in the far past some people installed
phpmyadmin. With good reasons back then but phpmyadmin has quite a list of
<a href="http://www.phpmyadmin.net/home_page/security/">security issues</a>.
They all get fixed, but we have to hunt down the old versions. So as a stopgap
I want to disable all urls on all vhosts which include <em>/phpmyadmin</em>.
Global config:
<pre>
RewriteEngine On
RewriteRule /phpmyadmin - [F,NC,L]
</pre>
But this isn't inherited by VirtualHosts immediately, as documented in
<a href="http://httpd.apache.org/docs/current/mod/mod_rewrite.html#vhosts">mod_rewrite and vhosts - Apache HTTP server documentation</a>. I need to
configure each vhost to inherit the global rewriterules:
<pre>
RewriteEngine On
RewriteOptions Inherit
</pre>
</blockquote>
